1. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with two-player games and payoff functions over infinite paths. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses optimal strategies and quantitative objectives. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper deals with computing weighted averages. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the properties of different payoff functions. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with control of infinite paths in games.
